eory of social justice translates into public policy. This important book, drawing on international experience and a distinguished panel of political philosophers and social scientists, addresses what the meaning of social justice is, and how it translates into the everyday concerns of public and social policy, in the context of both multiculturalism and globalisation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aPolitical planning. 0aSocial justice. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh1 aAdebowale, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBertram, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrighouse, Harry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurchardt, Tania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurchardt, Tania, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCraig, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraig, Gary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGordon, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKymlicka, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLister, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiachaud, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmuecker, Katie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwift, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolff, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Iris Marion, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators